  <description type="morphology">Plants 3.5–4 cm. Stems with branches common, attenuate, flagelliform; paraphyllia present, rare. Stem leaves (central) oblong, flat, 2.5–3 × 1.2–1.5 mm; margins entire proximally, slightly serrulate in apex; apex rounded-apiculate; costa double, short; alar cells oblong to short-quadrate; basal laminal cells linear to irregularly rectangular, 5–10 × 1–2 µm; distal medial cells long-rhomboidal, 24–60 × 4–6 µm; apical cells irregularly rhomboidal, 13–18(–24) × 4–6 µm. Sexual condition dioicous. Seta 0.7–1.2 cm. Capsule exserted.</description>
